race.comment: PURPLE ROSE (9) resumes and is in a strong Sydney barn. She's switched yards and was unlucky not to have cracked a win in her maiden preparation. Presents off trial wins at Hawkesbury and Randwick, and the speedy mare will skip over and likely lead. She's going to take beating. SILVER TOUCH (12) debuts for a leading local yard and missed a whisker in a recent trial at the track. Expect her to race boldly. LOVEHUNTER (7) showed plenty in town early doors but hasn't fired in three runs since switching to the Pepper yard. She improved the latest and may show more today. FLASHBACK TIME (10) tries hard. Has the inside gate and the bl;inkers on for the first time and they may spark her up.
